WEBVTT

02:41.843 --> 02:44.947
<i>Begin in three, two, one.</i>

02:45.313 --> 02:47.049
<i>You're cleared.</i>

02:55.491 --> 02:59.195
This place... it must end.

03:02.296 --> 03:03.532
Look at me.

03:04.532 --> 03:05.966
Look at me!

03:09.938 --> 03:11.340
I'm so afraid for you.

03:17.979 --> 03:21.849
You know,
I hear the future like a voice.

03:22.116 --> 03:23.652
Do you know what it says?

03:25.687 --> 03:28.490
It says that all of these men
will perish

03:28.556 --> 03:31.593
along with those who help them.

04:33.889 --> 04:35.524
<i>Complete, time recorded.</i>

04:35.723 --> 04:37.324
<i>Please leave, Mr. Carmichael.</i>

04:37.658 --> 04:39.627
<i>Mr. Veidt will be with you
in a moment</i>

04:39.694 --> 04:41.329
<i>to finish your evaluation.</i>

05:04.786 --> 05:07.021
You said you take
your coffee black, yes?

05:07.488 --> 05:10.592
Yeah. I prefer my food
untampered.

05:11.326 --> 05:13.661
Untampered?

05:14.196 --> 05:15.598
That's a way to put it.

05:16.031 --> 05:17.098
Untampered.

05:18.266 --> 05:19.266
I'm Joseph veidt.

05:19.367 --> 05:20.668
You're the one who contacted me?

05:20.836 --> 05:23.538
No. No, I'm the one
who sees the candidates.

05:23.605 --> 05:25.707
I'm the psychologist
of the family.

05:26.574 --> 05:28.610
Times like these,
I prove my usefulness.

05:29.310 --> 05:30.310
Sit down.

05:34.716 --> 05:36.285
Virtually no hesitation.

05:37.752 --> 05:39.788
This is the fastest time
we've seen.

05:41.557 --> 05:43.759
Jaden was programmed to defy,

05:44.093 --> 05:48.831
to evoke an empathy response.
Most people never take the shot.

05:50.199 --> 05:52.167
I know what's alive
and what isn't.

05:52.767 --> 05:54.637
Because we told you
that Jaden was a machine.

05:54.702 --> 05:56.137
But we could have lied to you.

05:57.271 --> 05:58.507
Then you would be a murderer.

05:59.173 --> 06:01.310
Then the veidt corporation
would be my accomplice.

06:01.910 --> 06:04.012
You make machines.
You said it was a machine.

06:05.079 --> 06:07.682
I usually find the simplest way
to look at things is best.

06:08.750 --> 06:10.319
You have military experience.

06:10.952 --> 06:12.587
Do you have problems
with authority?

06:12.954 --> 06:15.824
Anybody ever answer that
question with anything but a no?

06:17.625 --> 06:19.427
Do you have problems
with authority?

06:19.762 --> 06:21.163
No.

06:22.798 --> 06:24.867
You were a police detective.

06:26.168 --> 06:27.468
You retired.

06:28.235 --> 06:30.706
Uh. The file gives no reason
for your retirement.

06:31.540 --> 06:33.275
You're a top-ten listed company.

06:33.742 --> 06:35.343
I'm sure you found out
why I retired.

06:37.144 --> 06:39.180
Well, I would like
to hear it from you.

06:42.685 --> 06:44.685
During the apprehension
of an assailant...

06:44.920 --> 06:47.857
My partner and the assailant
were both fatally wounded.

06:49.024 --> 06:50.024
How?

06:50.091 --> 06:52.127
The assailant took
my partner hostage.

06:52.961 --> 06:54.796
I did not follow protocol.

06:55.730 --> 06:57.432
Why didn't you follow protocol?

07:05.975 --> 07:07.677
Do you regret what you did?

07:08.475 --> 07:09.778
I live with what I did.

07:14.449 --> 07:16.752
Instead of charging you
with a crime,

07:16.851 --> 07:19.153
the police department
allowed you to retire.

07:19.588 --> 07:20.890
Is that a problem?

07:21.357 --> 07:22.358
Not right now.

07:25.060 --> 07:29.131
We reached out to potential
hires through uncommon channels.

07:29.230 --> 07:32.701
It wards off some people.
Why did you respond?

07:33.168 --> 07:34.002
I need the money.

07:34.101 --> 07:35.804
Even though you don't know
what the job is?

07:36.572 --> 07:37.706
Still need the money.

07:38.107 --> 07:40.342
And if I told you the job
was killing someone,

07:40.408 --> 07:41.675
would that change your mind?

07:41.976 --> 07:44.713
Yeah. I'd tell you
to go fuck yourself.

07:45.747 --> 07:46.981
Hmm.

07:49.651 --> 07:51.754
My part of the evaluation
is done.

07:53.988 --> 07:55.924
You've earned the right
to meet my brother.

09:19.941 --> 09:21.277
Hello, David.

09:43.965 --> 09:47.570
Welcome to my humble empire.

10:08.190 --> 10:09.190
Come, come.

10:13.428 --> 10:15.163
The task is my daughter...

10:17.832 --> 10:19.033
Melissa.

10:21.102 --> 10:22.737
Three weeks ago,
she went missing.

10:23.504 --> 10:24.972
And you didn't go to the police?

10:25.405 --> 10:28.076
I don't need them
to find her for me.

10:29.043 --> 10:31.013
I know exactly where she is.

10:33.615 --> 10:35.884
I need someone discreet...

10:37.284 --> 10:42.290
Someone that won't ruin
pragmatism with principle.

10:43.557 --> 10:45.093
I'm not sure I understand.

10:45.827 --> 10:47.362
I'm sure you don't.

10:47.861 --> 10:49.197
Let me assist you.

10:49.998 --> 10:52.568
What do you know about zone 414?

10:55.669 --> 10:57.838
Well, that's the only place
where androids are allowed

10:57.905 --> 10:59.440
to freely interact
with human beings.

11:00.642 --> 11:02.076
My androids.

11:03.144 --> 11:04.178
Yeah.

11:09.350 --> 11:12.187
Do you know what I did
with my technology?

11:13.621 --> 11:16.224
I built the antidote

11:16.291 --> 11:19.295
to the loneliness
of the modern world.

11:20.995 --> 11:24.132
Companionship
is rare these days.

11:28.035 --> 11:30.605
I saw a gap, and I filled it.

11:41.149 --> 11:44.719
So the government
rewarded me with zone 414,

11:45.052 --> 11:47.788
a place where I could
field test my creations

11:47.922 --> 11:51.293
to see how they interact
with humanity.

11:51.993 --> 11:55.297
Zone 414, the city of robots.

11:55.529 --> 11:58.198
Have you been there?

11:59.167 --> 12:02.771
Uh. A cop's wage doesn't usually
afford luxuries, no.

12:03.004 --> 12:05.673
It has become quite
the destination, hasn't it?

12:05.807 --> 12:09.043
My little metropolitan Eden

12:09.211 --> 12:11.513
with all the grime
and none of the crime.

12:14.149 --> 12:17.184
I was advised to charge
100,000 pounds.

12:17.285 --> 12:20.288
I said,
"no, charge one million."

12:20.755 --> 12:21.956
Five days later...

12:22.456 --> 12:26.160
I had a six-month waiting list.

12:26.260 --> 12:28.161
For 20 million pounds,

12:28.229 --> 12:30.465
you could buy
one of my beautiful creations,

12:30.664 --> 12:33.501
and I sold 17 last year.

12:34.434 --> 12:37.838
Of course you have
to apply for a license,

12:37.938 --> 12:42.409
submit yourself to government
monitoring and blah-blah-blah.

12:42.710 --> 12:45.146
I didn't know it was legal
to have 'em outside the zone.

12:45.647 --> 12:47.516
It isn't for someone like you.

12:52.120 --> 12:53.522
Mr. Carmichael...

12:55.289 --> 12:57.525
My daughter is in zone 414,

12:57.592 --> 13:00.961
and I need you to retrieve her
for me...

13:01.028 --> 13:02.331
Without incident.

13:03.030 --> 13:05.866
You see, my Eden is fragile.

13:06.268 --> 13:09.738
It may look like a city,
but it is as much a construction

13:09.871 --> 13:12.707
as the machine
standing behind me.

13:15.309 --> 13:21.049
People must feel that the place
is safe... controlled.

13:21.883 --> 13:23.218
Police searching

13:23.317 --> 13:24.918
